<subSubSection id="C368652E93508E0DF2AAF8B5FDCBF866" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593508E0DF2AAF8B5FDCBF866" blockId="9.[151,1436,1831,2038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
The 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF2F4F8B5FEFAF88A" box="[201,299,1831,1857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">holotype</typeStatus>
of the species is a female already recognized as such by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF1A0F8B5FBECF88A" author="Sciaky, R." box="[925,1085,1831,1857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="29 - 120" refId="ref12184" refString="Sciaky, R. (1987) Revisione delle specie paleartiche occidentali del genere Ophonus Dejean, 1821. Memoria della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 65, 29 - 120." type="journal article" year="1987">Sciaky (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. He probably pinned a red label stating 
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF2D5F8D9FE9EF8AE" box="[232,335,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF2D5F8D9FE9EF8AE" box="[232,335,1867,1893]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
in this specimen. Therefore, it presently bears the following labels: white labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693508E0DF6EFF8D9FA49F8AE" authority="Dahl" authorityName="Dahl" box="[1234,1432,1867,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricollis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF6EFF8D9FA88F8AE" box="[1234,1369,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">quadricollis</emphasis>
Dahl
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F84793508E0DF28EF8FDFF2AF842" box="[179,251,1903,1929]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Sicilia</collectingRegion>
alp. D.” “Dahl”, “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF3FBF8FDFDB2F842" box="[454,611,1903,1929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
”. I have added a white label “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF195F8FDFBC2F842" box="[936,1043,1903,1929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693508E0DF605F8FDFE81F866" authority="Dejean, 1831" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricollis" subGenus="Ophonus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF605F8FDFF60F866" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Harpalus (Ophonus) quadricollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF284F801FE81F866" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[185,336,1939,1965]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" refId="ref10829" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1831) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome cinquieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, viii + 883 pp." type="book" year="1831">Dejean, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, J. Serrano vidit”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93508E0EF2FAF825FB92FF1E" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="494" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593508E0DF2FAF825FBE9F83E" blockId="9.[151,1436,1831,2038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893508E0DF2FAF825FBE5F83E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147323" collectorName="M. Dahl" location="Sicile" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sicilia">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF2FAF825FEB6F81A" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[199,359,1975,2001]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
wrote: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF387F82AFBE5F83E" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
Je ne possède qu’un individu femelle de cet insecte, qui m’a été envoyé par 
<collectorName id="2687537393508E0DF6C6F82AFA89F81A" box="[1275,1368,1975,2001]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">M. Dahl</collectorName>
, sous le nom spécifique que je lui ai conservé, comme venant des montagnes de la 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F84793508E0DF1CFF849FBE5F83E" box="[1010,1076,2011,2037]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Sicile</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
</materialsCitation>
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF609F849FBE9F83E" box="[1076,1080,2011,2037]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593538E0EF2FAFF05FB92FF1E" blockId="10.[151,1436,150,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF2FAFF05FEB6FF7A" author="Sciaky, R." box="[199,359,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" pagination="29 - 120" refId="ref12184" refString="Sciaky, R. (1987) Revisione delle specie paleartiche occidentali del genere Ophonus Dejean, 1821. Memoria della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 65, 29 - 120." type="journal article" year="1987">Sciaky (1987)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the taxonomic problems concerning this species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF628FF05FB13FF7A" author="Antoine, M." box="[1045,1218,150,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF6C1FF05FA4DFF7A" author="Sciaky, R." box="[1276,1436,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" pagination="29 - 120" refId="ref12184" refString="Sciaky, R. (1987) Revisione delle specie paleartiche occidentali del genere Ophonus Dejean, 1821. Memoria della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 65, 29 - 120." type="journal article" year="1987">Sciaky (1987)</bibRefCitation>
made up keys to identify the species. It is a Siculo-Maghrebian geographic element.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
